# This file describes creating a new Jenkins job and configuring it to use Python.

1. Click on "create new jobs" on Dashboard.

2. Enter the name of the project and check "Freestyle project".

3. Under "Build" tab, select "Python Builder".

4. Select "Nature" as "Python".

5. Type "Python" in "Command" field.

6. Configure appropriate "Post-Build actions" if required.
